<p>Then, we <em>do</em> need a password field, but think about it: the property we want to
set on <code>User</code> is <em>not</em> actually the <code>password</code> property. We need to set <code>plainPassword</code>.
Add this. It'll be a password type. But, if you want the user to type the password
twice, use a <code>RepeatedType</code>. Then, in the third argument, pass the real type with
<code>type</code> set to <code>PasswordType::class</code>:</p>
