<p>That'll render <em>two</em> password boxes. And if the values don't match, validation will
automatically fail.</p>
<h2 id="rendering-the-form">Rendering the Form <a class="headerlink" href="user-registration-form#rendering-the-form" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Form done! In the controller, start with <code>$form = $this-&gt;createForm()</code>. And of course,
make sure you're extending the Symfony base Controller! Then, pass this
<code>UserRegistrationForm::class</code>:</p>
